  "body": "### Overview\r\nI am getting this error on hardhat branch when a transaction is reverted:\r\n`ipdb> history[-1].events\r\n*** brownie.exceptions.RPCRequestError: Accessing `TransactionReceipt.events` on a reverted transaction requires the `debug_traceTransaction` RPC endpoint, but the node client does not support it or has not made it available.\r\n`\r\nWhat is the current way to debug transactions on hardhat-fork network. I am not very familiar with hardhad.\r\nIt would be great of someone can point me to best practices for debugging solidity.\r\n\r\nMy goal is to have a fast feedback loop during contract development when it needs to interact with forked network.\r\nThanks.\r\n",
